    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-08-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="358"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Van Valkenburgh</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 78.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Yokohama,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-08-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 3, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to transmit herewith inclosure
                    No. 1, a copy of letter from Higashi Kuze Chinjio, minister for foreign affairs,
                    informing me that from the 1st of September next Osaka will be a port of
                    entry.</p>
                <p>Among the foreign merchants at Hiogo and Osaka, the opinions of the relative
                    future importance of those two places have been much divided, and by this
                    measure they are now placed on a par.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R. B. VAN VALKENBURGH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <pb facs="0834" n="786" xml:id="pg_786"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <p>To His Excellency <hi rend="smallcaps">R. B. Van Vankenburgh</hi>, <hi
                            rend="italic">Minister Resident of the United States, &amp;c., &amp;c.,
                            &amp;c.:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>I have the honor to inform you that it has been determined to make Osaka a
                        port of entry from the 15th day of the 7th month of this year, Ke Wo, as
                        agreed upon at my recent conference with all the foreign
                        representatives.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">On <date calendar="gregorian japanese-nengō"
                                when="1868-07-25">the 6th day of the 6th month—July 25,
                            1868</date>.</dateline>
                        <lb/>
                        <signed>HIGASHI KUZE CHINJIO.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
